Body:
tldr;
They charged me $80 cad not through the Apple and went no contact. Absolutely non-existent customer service.

I used reflectly for a week or so last year, then I deleted the app and forgot about it until 2 weeks ago, when a charge by reflectly for $80 appeared on my credit card. It was not an Apple subscription, it was billed directly by reflectly. I reinstalled the app just in case I forgot to cancel something - nope, no premium, nothing. Also no receipt anywhere. What’s more astounding is that they refuse to help. I reached out to their tech support, they said they will look into it and stopped responding to me for a week now. I had to file a fraud complaint with my credit card company, since reflectly is not responding. You’d think taking peoples money without their consent or without providing them with services for that money would be a bigger issue for them, alas I have no faith that they care.
